king and its vital role in society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  a1910s, movie, film, movie stars, Charlie Chaplin, Mary Pickford, Pearl White, Sessue Hayakawa, Theda Bara, American filmmaking, G. M. Anderson'.1 aAbel, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbel, Richard.1 aBean, Jennifer M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBean, Jennifer M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBertellini, Giorgio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBertellini, Giorgio.1 aCooper, Mark Garrett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Mark.1 aCurtis, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurtis, Scott.1 aGledhill, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGledhill, Christine.1 aGrant, Kristen.1 aHatch, Kristen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Rob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Rob.1 aMiyao, Daisuke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiyao, Daisuke.1 aMorey, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorey, Anne.1 aStudlar, Gaylyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStudlar, Gaylyn.1 aWhissel, Kristen.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081355072540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813550725423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813550725/original 